sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor C as Client
    participant GW as API Gateway
    participant KC as Keycloak<br/>(JWKS)
    participant TX as Transaction<br/>Service
    participant IDEMP as IdempotencyService<br/>(unique index)
    participant MONGO as MongoDB<br/>(replica set)
    participant OUT as Outbox<br/>Publisher
    participant KAFKA as Kafka<br/>tx.completed

    Note over C,GW: Headers required:<br/>Authorization: Bearer <jwt><br/>Idempotency-Key: <uuid>

    C->>GW: POST /v1/transactions/transfer<br/>{src, dst, amount, currency}

    rect rgba(254, 243, 199, 0.5)
      Note over GW: Edge concerns
      GW->>KC: validate JWT signature<br/>(JWKS, cached)
      KC-->>GW: ok / scopes / sub
      GW->>GW: rate-limit check<br/>scope check (transfer:write)
    end

    GW->>TX: forward request<br/>+ X-Correlation-Id

    rect rgba(220, 252, 231, 0.5)
      Note over TX,MONGO: Single MongoDB transaction<br/>all-or-nothing
      TX->>IDEMP: lookup by (userId, "transfer", key)
      IDEMP->>MONGO: find one in `transactions`
      alt Existing — same payload (replay)
        MONGO-->>IDEMP: original tx doc
        IDEMP-->>TX: return original
        TX-->>GW: 200 OK + original response
        GW-->>C: 200 OK + original response
        Note over C,TX: Idempotent replay — no DB writes
      else Existing — different payload
        TX-->>GW: 409 /problems/idempotency-key-conflict
        GW-->>C: 409 Conflict
      else No existing record
        TX->>MONGO: BEGIN TRANSACTION

        TX->>MONGO: conditional debit on source<br/>updateOne({_id:src, balance:{$gte:amt}, status:ACTIVE},<br/> {$inc:{balance:-amt}, $inc:{version:1}})

        alt matchedCount == 0
          MONGO-->>TX: no match
          TX->>MONGO: ABORT
          TX-->>GW: 422 /problems/insufficient-funds<br/>or /problems/account-unavailable
          GW-->>C: 422 Unprocessable Entity
        else matched
          MONGO-->>TX: ok
          TX->>MONGO: credit destination<br/>(updateOne with version check)
          MONGO-->>TX: ok
          TX->>MONGO: insert 2 journal lines<br/>(DEBIT on src, CREDIT on dst)
          MONGO-->>TX: ok
          TX->>MONGO: insert transactions doc<br/>(idempotencyKey, status=COMPLETED, journalLineIds)
          MONGO-->>TX: ok (unique-index enforces idempotency)
          TX->>MONGO: insert outbox row<br/>(topic=tx.completed, payload=event)
          MONGO-->>TX: ok
          TX->>MONGO: COMMIT
          MONGO-->>TX: committed
          TX-->>GW: 201 Created + TransferResponse
          GW-->>C: 201 Created
        end
      end
    end

    Note over OUT,KAFKA: Asynchronous — does NOT block the response<br/>Polling worker, ~200ms tick

    loop every ~200ms
      OUT->>MONGO: find outbox where status=PENDING<br/>order by createdAt limit N
      MONGO-->>OUT: batch
      OUT->>KAFKA: send(topic, key=transactionId, value=event)
      KAFKA-->>OUT: ack (acks=all)
      OUT->>MONGO: mark outbox row SENT
    end

    Note over TX,OUT: If TX commits then publisher crashes:<br/>row stays PENDING → republished on next tick<br/>If Kafka acks then publisher crashes before mark SENT:<br/>row republished → duplicate in Kafka<br/>→ consumers dedupe by eventId (inbox pattern)
